---
// src/components/Section2ProblemAgitateSolve.astro
---
<section id="problem" class="py-16 md:py-24 bg-gradient-to-b from-[#0a0a15] to-[#0c0c18] px-4 md:px-8">
    <div class="container mx-auto max-w-3xl">
        <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-extrabold text-white text-center mb-12 tracking-tight leading-none" data-animate="fade" data-delay="100">
            The Bottleneck Holding Your Music Back
        </h2>

        <div class="card-gradient p-8 md:p-10 rounded-2xl shadow-glass border border-gray-800/20 mb-8" data-animate="fade" data-delay="200">
            <!-- Problem Section -->
            <div class="space-y-4 mb-8">
                <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
                    <div class="bg-pulse-purple/10 p-2 rounded-lg">
                        <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="w-7 h-7 text-pulse-purple" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
                            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M12 9v2m0 4h.01m-6.938 4h13.856c1.54 0 2.502-1.667 1.732-3L13.732 4c-.77-1.333-2.694-1.333-3.464 0L3.34 16c-.77 1.333.192 3 1.732 3z" />
                        </svg>
                    </div>
                    <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white">The Problem</h3>
                </div>
                <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
                    You've spent countless hours watching tutorials. Your plugin folder is overflowing. You've read all the articles and taken the courses.
                </p>
                <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
                    And yet when you compare your tracks to professional releases, something's still missing. The low end isn't as powerful. The vocals don't cut through. The overall sound lacks that polished quality that separates amateur productions from commercial releases.
                </p>
            </div>

            <!-- Linear divider -->
            <div class="w-full h-px bg-gradient-to-r from-pulse-purple/10 via-gray-700/30 to-pulse-cyan/10 my-8"></div>

            <!-- Frustration Section -->
            <div class="space-y-4 mb-8">
                <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
                    <div class="bg-pulse-purple/10 p-2 rounded-lg">
                        <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="w-7 h-7 text-pulse-purple" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
                            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M13 10V3L4 14h7v7l9-11h-7z" />
                        </svg>
                    </div>
                    <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white">The Frustration</h3>
                </div>
                <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
                    You can't even identify exactly what's wrong â€“ let alone how to fix it. Without a clear direction, you're left guessing, making random changes based on conflicting advice, and hoping something works.
                </p>
                <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
                    Meanwhile, months turn into years as your music stays stuck at that "almost there" level.
                </p>
                <div class="bg-[#080810] p-4 rounded-lg border-l-4 border-pulse-cyan mt-4 shadow-inner-glow">
                    <p class="font-bold text-pulse-cyan">WARNING:</p>
                    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300">Without objective data, you'll spend years guessing what's wrong with your mixes instead of knowing exactly what to fix.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Linear divider -->
            <div class="w-full h-px bg-gradient-to-r from-pulse-purple/10 via-gray-700/30 to-pulse-cyan/10 my-8"></div>

            <!-- Solution Section -->
            <div class="space-y-4">
                <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
                    <div class="bg-pulse-purple/10 p-2 rounded-lg">
                        <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="w-7 h-7 text-pulse-purple" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
                            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M9 12l2 2 4-4m5.618-4.016A11.955 11.955 0 0112 2.944a11.955 11.955 0 01-8.618 3.04A12.02 12.02 0 003 9c0 5.591 3.824 10.29 9 11.622 5.176-1.332 9-6.03 9-11.622 0-1.042-.133-2.052-.382-3.016z" />
                        </svg>
                    </div>
                    <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white">The Solution</h3>
                </div>
                <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
                    What if you could see exactly how professional tracks are constructed, all the way down to the individual stems? What if you could analyze the precise mix balance and sonic characteristics that make hit records sound the way they do?
                </p>
                <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
                    Using specialized AI tools, we break down professional tracks into their core components, measure them objectively, and show you precisely how to apply these findings to your music.
                </p>
                <p class="font-semibold text-xl text-white mt-4 mb-8 bg-gradient-to-r from-pulse-purple/20 to-pulse-cyan/20 p-4 rounded-lg">
                    No more guesswork. Just clear, measurable paths to professional-quality productions.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section> 